The paper deals with optimizing the evaluation of queries in MapReduce, which is a common technique used in distributed databases and data processing systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel multi-semi-join operator, which is a computational problem and falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses optimizations aimed at minimizing total time, which is a problem in scheduling and falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also presents experiments and results, which is a common theme in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
